## v1.0.0 — 2026-06-13

Initial version. Documents planning patterns for nested-marker test coverage of
`get_repo_root()`. Covers four cross-combination test cases (git+git,
pyproject+pyproject, git+pyproject, pyproject+git) with inline `tmp_path`
layout construction. Three failed attempts documented: shared fixture,
single-representative test, and seed placed at the marker level. Verification
status: unverified (plan only, tests not run).

---

## v1.1.0 — 2026-06-13

Added a fourth **Failed Attempt** identified during a plan review (NOGO R0→R1
cycle): asserting `get_repo_root(seed) == inner` against an unresolved
`tmp_path` subpath. The fix is to always use `== inner.resolve()` because
`get_repo_root()` calls `Path(start_path).resolve()` at helpers.py:117, making
its return value always a resolved path. On CI environments where `$TMPDIR` is
a symlink, `inner != inner.resolve()` causes spurious assertion failures.

All four test-body assertions in the Proposed Workflow updated from
`== inner` to `== inner.resolve()`. `history` frontmatter field added pointing
to this file.
